
Clients may have several questions regarding payments when engaging with a web developer or service provider. Here are some common questions they might ask:

What are your payment terms?
How much does the service cost?
Do you require a deposit upfront?
What payment methods do you accept?
Is there a payment schedule for larger projects?
Are there any additional fees or hidden costs?
Do you offer any discounts or promotions for long-term contracts or bundled services?
What is your refund policy?
When is payment due?
Can I receive an invoice for the services provided?
Is there a late payment policy?
Do you offer payment plans for larger projects or ongoing services?
Are there any tax implications for the payments?
Is there a contract or agreement outlining the payment terms?
What happens if I need to make changes to the project scope or timeline?
Do you offer payment options for international clients?
Can I pay in installments as the project progresses?
How do you handle payments for ongoing maintenance or support services?
What currency do you invoice in?
Can I receive a breakdown of costs for each phase of the project?












